parameters.description: Log intrinsic growth rate for phytoplankton nutrient uptake (day^-1). (Initial value corresponds to r ~ 0.1 day^-1)
Log half-saturation constant for nutrient limitation (g C m^-3). (Initial value corresponds to K ~ 1 g C m^-3)
Log maximum grazing rate by zooplankton (day^-1). (Initial value corresponds to g_max ~ 0.1 day^-1)
Log half-saturation constant for zooplankton grazing functional response (g C m^-3). (Initial value corresponds to K_P ~ 1 g C m^-3)
Log assimilation efficiency; fraction of grazed phytoplankton converted into zooplankton biomass (dimensionless). (Initial value corresponds to e ~ 0.9)
Log mortality rate for phytoplankton (day^-1). (Initial value corresponds to m_P ~ 0.05 day^-1)
Log mortality rate for zooplankton (day^-1). (Initial value corresponds to m_Z ~ 0.05 day^-1)
Log observation error standard deviation for nutrient data (log-scale).
Log observation error standard deviation for phytoplankton data (log-scale).
Log observation error standard deviation for zooplankton data (log-scale).
